<h1>Consumer Rights in India</h1>

<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>Consumers in India are protected under the Consumer Protection Act 2019, which safeguards their rights and provides legal remedies.</p>

<h2>Rights of Consumers</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Right to Safety</li>
  <li>Right to Information</li>
  <li>Right to Choose</li>
  <li>Right to be Heard</li>
  <li>Right to Redress</li>
  <li>Right to Consumer Education</li>
</ul>

<h2>How to File a Complaint</h2>
<p>Consumers can file complaints with the Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission at District, State, or National levels.</p>

